data.name: Classic Patty Melt
data.quickTastyDescription: A deliciously cheesy burger sandwich grilled to perfection, combining the flavors of beef, melty cheese, and caramelized onions.
detailedCookingInstructions: Heat a skillet over medium heat and melt 1 tablespoon of butter.
Add sliced onions and sauté until they are golden brown, about 5-7 minutes. Remove from skillet and set aside.
In the same skillet, form two patties with the ground beef, season with salt and pepper, and cook for about 4-5 minutes on each side until cooked to your liking.
Place a slice of Swiss cheese on each patty and allow it to melt.
Butter one side of each slice of rye bread and place two slices butter-side-down in the skillet.
Layer the cooked patties with melted cheese and sautéed onions on top of the bread in the skillet, then cover with the remaining slices of bread, butter-side-up.
Grill the sandwiches for about 3-4 minutes on each side until golden brown and crispy. Slice in half and serve immediately.
